What you need to know:  The crop requires plenty of water, therefore, the family dug a borehole at a cost of Sh150,000 for a constant water supply.If well-taken care of, the plants start producing fruits in about eight weeks, and they will then change from green to bright yellow. Harvesting continues for over two months.They sell them at Marikiti market in Mombasa at Sh80 each. The melons weigh between 2.3 and 2.85 kilos each.